reviews.review: I'm one of these "original Star Wars" fans that has tons of opinions to tell you if I find a gap in any conversation. So glad JJ Abrams came back and did this final movie in the trilogy. Makes me wish he'd done The Last Jedi, too. Go see this. The critics have it all wrong. This movie is fun.
not bad fitting end to the franchise, corrected alot of wrongs from past movies.

As a stand alone movie it is emotive and entertaining. Special effects on top the game as usual......but.... as a Star Wars fan I wasn't pleased at all with the twist! The story is supposed to be of the Skywalker family. Why in the hell did they give the Jedi torch to a Palpatine is beyond me!? I'm too much of a loyalist to the original story to give this movie a high rating. The story to me was everything!

Una falta de respeto a toda la historia antetior, la fuerza, que es la esencia de las películas, ahora no es la fuerza, es algo distinto. Esta trilogía no es una secuela de las anteriores, es algo nuevo. No deberían llamarse Star Wars. La película se siente forzada en cada escena, tratando de arreglar los daños irreparables del episodio anterior
I thought it was a really good ending to the trilogy . It wasn’t perfect but I still enjoyed it.

I was both looking and not looking forward to this movie. I was one of those disappointed by TLJ.  There were moments in this movie that I loved and moments that made me go "wtf" and at one point I laughed out loud during what was not a funny moment.  I just found it to be ridiculous and the laugh just spilled out of me.  

Was this a glorious end to the Skywalker Saga?  No, but it is passable after you've thought about it and discussed it with friends.  It is not the dumpster fire that others are making it out to be.  

The cast were great, but adding so many new characters to the last chapter of this trilogy was maybe not the best idea.  I'd watch it again.
It was ok, they closed this chapter. The next needs better story telling and action.
A sad way to end but a must see....enjoyed every minute of it
It was very good and wrapped up the story.
seemed like a puzzle finished with the wrong piece trying to get passed off in hurry
